---
export const prerender = true;

import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import SessionBar from '../components/SessionBar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | PATAPIM" description="The story behind Patapim, told by the person who built it.">
  <Navbar />
  <SessionBar />

  <main class="about-page">

    <!-- Opening -->
    <section class="about-intro">
      <div class="container-narrow">
        <div class="tv-label"><span class="tv-label-prompt">$</span> patapim about <span class="tv-dim">— why this exists</span></div>
        <h1 class="intro-headline">Working with AI agents is a new discipline.<br/>It needs a <span class="tv-grad">new kind of tool.</span></h1>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The problem & the method -->
    <section class="about-story">
      <div class="container-narrow">

        <h3 class="story-subtitle"><span class="story-prompt">▸</span> The concentration problem</h3>
        <p class="story-text">
          You give an agent a task. Then you wait. That idle time is where <strong>concentration breaks</strong>. You drift, you check something else, and by the time the agent finishes, you've lost the context you needed. The problem isn't the AI. <strong>Waiting is fundamentally incompatible with staying focused.</strong>
        </p>

        <h3 class="story-subtitle"><span class="story-prompt">▸</span> Structured multitasking</h3>
        <p class="story-text">
          The solution: <strong>don't wait. Launch multiple agents at once.</strong> One works on a migration, another writes tests, another refactors a component. You <em>orchestrate</em>: review what's done, redirect what's off track, launch the next thing. <strong>The agents handle execution. You handle direction.</strong> The bottleneck was never intelligence. It's workflow.
        </p>

        <h3 class="story-subtitle"><span class="story-prompt">▸</span> Voice over typing</h3>
        <p class="story-text">
          Typing forces you to <strong>linearize your thinking before you've finished thinking</strong>. It's slow, unnatural, and it burns energy. Voice lets you think out loud, verbalize the need as it forms. <strong>Removing the friction between thought and instruction</strong> changes everything.
        </p>

        <h3 class="story-subtitle"><span class="story-prompt">▸</span> Structure over chaos</h3>
        <p class="story-text">
          Most LLM workflows are one long, unstructured conversation. No separation between projects, tasks, or contexts. Real work is <strong>folder-based</strong>: every task belongs to a project, every project has its own context. A tool that ignores this is fighting you.
        </p>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What Patapim is -->
    <section class="about-why">
      <div class="container-narrow">
        <div class="tv-label"><span class="tv-label-prompt">$</span> patapim --help <span class="tv-dim">— what it is</span></div>
        <div class="why-block">
          <h2>A framework for structured multi-agent work</h2>
          <p>
            Patapim is an organizational framework for working with multiple AI agents. Multiple agents side by side, with <strong>instant notifications</strong> when tasks finish. A dashboard showing what's in progress and what's done. <strong>Voice dictation</strong> to think out loud. <strong>Folder-based projects</strong> with persistent context. Session recovery.
          </p>
          <div class="why-callout tv-panel tv-panel-static">
            <p>A <strong>built-in browser</strong> your agents can control directly, all within the same framework. Gmail, WhatsApp, dashboards, web apps. If it runs in a browser, your agents can automate it.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="why-callout tv-panel tv-panel-static">
            <p>Everything runs on your local machine. <strong>Remote access with voice dictation</strong> means you can keep directing your agents from anywhere. Walking, commuting, away from your desk. You dictate from your phone, the agents execute on your computer. You never stop working just because you stepped away.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 3DAR -->
    <section class="about-3dar">
      <div class="container-narrow">
        <div class="tv-label"><span class="tv-label-prompt">$</span> whoami <span class="tv-dim">— the person behind it</span></div>
        <div class="dar-header">
          <img src="/german-heller.jpg" alt="German Heller" class="dar-portrait" width="200" height="200" loading="lazy" />
          <div>
            <a href="https://3dar.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="dar-logo-link">
              <img src="/3dar-logo.svg" alt="3DAR logo" class="dar-logo" />
            </a>
            <h2 class="section-break-title">About me & 3DAR</h2>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="dar-text">
          I'm the co-founder and CEO of <a href="https://3dar.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">3DAR</a>, an animation and VFX studio based in Buenos Aires and Santa Monica since 2004. We've worked with Disney, Google, Meta, Sony, Bad Bunny, Colin Farrell, Edward Norton. Premiered at Sundance, won at Venice, got an Emmy nomination. Fast Company named us the #2 most innovative company in Latin America.
        </p>
        <p class="dar-text">
          Patapim came out of that same obsession with making things work better. I built it for myself, and now I'd like to share it with anyone who finds it useful.
        </p>

        <div class="dar-reel">
          <video
            autoplay
            muted
            loop
            playsinline
            preload="auto"
            poster="https://3dar-site.s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/versions/covers/960x540/cUS54m4vm66Sn3w2LhHvpWGr8y0X7zSR2X7T8Anv.webp"
          >
            <source src="https://player.vimeo.com/progressive_redirect/playback/1123995054/rendition/540p/file.mp4?loc=external&log_user=0&signature=266e47614cbe436f221290d45a418de2c3cfc796e5891dfe9201b9aa19cb0019" type="video/mp4" />
          </video>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Links -->
    <section class="about-find-me">
      <div class="container-narrow">
        <p class="find-me-text">Find me around the internet:</p>
        <div class="find-me-links">
          <a href="https://germanheller.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">germanheller.com</a>
          <span class="link-sep">/</span>
          <a href="https://3dar.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">3dar.com</a>
          <span class="link-sep">/</span>
          <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/german-heller-35500a8" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>
          <span class="link-sep">/</span>
          <a href="https://imdb.com/name/nm5265626" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IMDb</a>
        </div>
        <a href="/download" class="tv-bigcta about-download">
          <span>$ download patapim</span>
          <span class="tv-bigcta-cursor">█</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    padding-bottom: 96px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    background: var(--bg-deep);
  }

  .container-narrow {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 24px;
  }

  /* Intro */
  .about-intro {
    padding-top: 140px;
    padding-bottom: 64px;
  }

  .intro-headline {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-size: clamp(24px, 4.4vw, 38px);
    line-height: 1.3;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: 10px 0 0;
  }

  /* Story */
  .about-story {
    padding-bottom: 64px;
  }

  .story-subtitle {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    margin: 48px 0 12px;
    background: var(--p-gradient);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
  }

  .story-prompt {
    -webkit-text-fill-color: var(--vi);
  }

  .story-subtitle:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .story-text {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.95;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .story-text strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .story-text em {
    color: var(--cy);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .section-break-title {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  /* Why */
  .about-why {
    padding: 64px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  .why-block h2 {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .why-block p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.95;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }

  .why-block p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .why-callout {
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }

  .why-callout p {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.9;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* 3DAR Section */
  .about-3dar {
    padding: 64px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  .dar-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 24px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .dar-portrait {
    width: 80px;
    height: 80px;
    border-radius: 0;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center 15%;
    filter: grayscale(1);
    opacity: 0.85;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-default);
  }

  .dar-header .section-break-title {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .dar-logo-link {
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .dar-logo {
    width: 110px;
    height: auto;
    filter: brightness(0) invert(1);
    opacity: 0.7;
    transition: opacity 150ms;
  }

  .dar-logo-link:hover .dar-logo {
    opacity: 1;
  }

  .dar-text {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.95;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .dar-text a {
    color: var(--cy);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
    transition: border-color 150ms;
  }

  .dar-text a:hover {
    border-bottom-color: var(--cy);
  }

  .dar-reel {
    margin-top: 32px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-default);
    overflow: hidden;
    max-width: 540px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .dar-reel video {
    width: 100%;
    display: block;
  }

  /* Find Me */
  .about-find-me {
    padding: 48px 0 64px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .find-me-text {
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    font-size: 13px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .find-me-links {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }

  .find-me-links a {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 14px;
    transition: color 150ms;
  }

  .find-me-links a:hover {
    color: var(--cy);
  }

  .link-sep {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 13px;
  }

  .about-download {
    display: inline-flex;
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .about-intro {
      padding-top: 120px;
    }

    .intro-headline br {
      display: none;
    }

    .find-me-links {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 8px;
    }

    .link-sep {
      display: none;
    }
  }
</style>
